00:27:54,910 --> 00:27:57,290
Why are you behaving like this with your future husband?

548
00:27:57,370 --> 00:27:58,750
I am behaving the way I should.

549
00:27:58,870 --> 00:28:00,250
Adi. - Fine, I am going.

550
00:28:00,370 --> 00:28:03,120
At least give me a kiss before I go. - No, Adi.

551
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:04,290
Just go.

552
00:28:05,370 --> 00:28:06,750
What's this? - What?

553
00:28:07,620 --> 00:28:08,790
Adi.. !

554
00:28:09,120 --> 00:28:11,250
You're so.. cute.

555
00:28:14,540 --> 00:28:15,750
Where is it?

556
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:18,790
Sweety, where's the flush?

557
00:28:19,160 --> 00:28:20,910
These days they've sensors.

558
00:28:21,000 --> 00:28:23,410
Wave your hand under the tap and the water comes out.

559
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:25,250
But what do I wave here?

560
00:28:25,620 --> 00:28:27,000
My head.

561
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:29,000
Oh, God.. what did you give me?

562
00:28:29,250 --> 00:28:30,290
Coming.

563
00:28:31,660 --> 00:28:33,040
You're just.. - What?

564
00:28:33,120 --> 00:28:34,120
Too much.

565
00:28:35,040 --> 00:28:37,410
Sensor. Sensor. - Yeah, sensor.

566
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:40,000
What are you two doing in the bathroom together?

567
00:28:40,250 --> 00:28:44,500
We're playing a game, but you should've knocked before coming in.

568
00:28:45,120 --> 00:28:46,790
Why? You two are not on a honeymoon here..

569
00:28:46,870 --> 00:28:47,910
..that you'll get disturbed.

570
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:49,120
Listen to that..

571
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:51,660
He isn't even married yet, and he's already got questions.

572
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:55,120
I wonder what's going to happen after the marriage.

573
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:56,870
He's my son.

574
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,910
He'll do good even after the marriage.

575
00:28:59,370 --> 00:29:01,540
Look, Adi.. your father-in-law might be..

576
00:29:01,620 --> 00:29:03,620
..a big manufacturer of motorcycles.

577
00:29:03,660 --> 00:29:06,000
But we Sodhis are no less.

578
00:29:06,410 --> 00:29:08,290
Your father's absolutely right.

579
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:10,040
Don't be scared of Riya.

580
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:12,750
Mom.. I am not a coward like papa.

581
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:16,160
Naughty. - Adi, you're feeling really brave now..

582
00:29:16,250 --> 00:29:19,290
..but by the time your honeymoon's over, you'll be tamed..

583
00:29:19,370 --> 00:29:20,620
..or else you can change my name.

584
00:29:21,250 --> 00:29:25,120
By the way.. this is a really romantic place.

585
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:27,660
So.. - I say we should not waste any time.

586
00:29:27,870 --> 00:29:29,120
It's the modern age..

587
00:29:29,250 --> 00:29:32,370
Bed her.. before the marriage.

588
00:29:33,290 --> 00:29:34,750
Riya doesn't like these things, papa.

589
00:29:35,910 --> 00:29:38,870
This means you've been thinking about it.

590
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:43,250
That's like a Sodhi. Give me a hug, son.

591
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:45,370
What are you teaching your son?

592
00:29:45,500 --> 00:29:48,620
I am teaching him something I couldn't learn myself.

593
00:29:48,870 --> 00:29:50,750
Come on, family hug.

594
00:29:50,870 --> 00:29:52,120
You're too much.

595
00:30:05,290 --> 00:30:08,910
Gulabo.. - What are you doing?

596
00:30:10,370 --> 00:30:14,250
I am so excited, I never thought I'll get married so quickly.

597
00:30:14,290 --> 00:30:17,870
Yeah.. looking at your actions, it's hard to say you're getting married.

598
00:30:27,370 --> 00:30:29,790
Tell me something.. have you finished preparing.

599
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:36,370
You're missing mom-dad too, aren't you?

600
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:40,120
I am missing them too.

601
00:30:41,370 --> 00:30:46,910
You know.. if they were here, they would've been so excited.. - Why?

602
00:30:48,790 --> 00:30:50,620
Did I leave any void, dear?

603
00:30:51,620 --> 00:30:52,750
No, Gulabo?

604
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,910
So tell me.. do you remember..

605
00:30:59,290 --> 00:31:02,160
..who was your first childhood friend?

606
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:04,500
You!

607
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:08,120
And who endured your tantrums?

608
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:10,500
You did, Gulabo!

609
00:31:10,750 --> 00:31:15,250
And remember, who made you taste whiskey first?

610
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,250
Of course, it can only be you.

611
00:31:20,870 --> 00:31:22,040
I am sorry.

612
00:31:22,370 --> 00:31:23,410
You're the best.

613
00:31:25,290 --> 00:31:29,500
Look, don't ever say such things again and hurt me.

614
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
When my heart aches, I need my medicine.

615
00:31:33,120 --> 00:31:35,120
What? What medicine?

616
00:31:36,410 --> 00:31:39,120
Oh my, God.. Gulabo, you're too much.

617
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:40,620
You want.

618
00:31:45,120 --> 00:31:52,000
Punjabi folk song.

619
00:31:52,370 --> 00:31:54,290
I love all this, so pretty.

620
00:31:54,870 --> 00:31:59,040
Listen.. was your Ravinder always like this..

621
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:01,000
..or did he become like this now?

622
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:02,000
What do you mean?

623
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:06,410
Don't mind.. but he looks a bit lusty to me.

624
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:13,790
I doubt.. he troubled you a lot on your first night.

625
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,620
Tell me the truth.

626
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:20,370
No, no.. he couldn't do a thing. - Why? Was he drunk?

627
00:32:20,500 --> 00:32:24,120
No, no.. when he came to me at night, I started crying.

628
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,620
I said 'I am missing my mom'.

629
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:29,120
He kept cajoling me all night.

630
00:32:30,910 --> 00:32:34,540
No wonder he's been venting his wedding night frustration till now.

631
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:38,370
Granny, you're just..

632
00:32:38,910 --> 00:32:41,370
Granny, it must be different during your time, isn't it?

633
00:32:41,500 --> 00:32:43,120
I mean.. did people go on honeymoon?

634
00:32:43,250 --> 00:32:44,870
We never went anywhere.

635
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:47,620
We would do it at every opportunity we got.

636
00:32:47,660 --> 00:32:50,620
You're too much, granny. - She's just too much.

637
00:32:50,750 --> 00:32:54,910
Oh my, God! They're so openly talking about their honeymoon.

638
00:32:55,370 --> 00:32:59,620
Like.. I'm not going to tell them.. what will happen on my honeymoon.

639
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:01,910
Oh really.. as if we don't know..

640
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:03,290
..what's going to happen on your honeymoon.

641
00:33:05,250 --> 00:33:05,790
Sorry.

642
00:33:05,870 --> 00:33:06,750
Sweety. - Yes.

643
00:33:06,870 --> 00:33:09,500
Where did you go on your honeymoon? - I went to Goa.

644
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:11,500
What did you see?

645
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:13,620
I didn't see anything in Goa? - Why?

646
00:33:13,750 --> 00:33:16,000
I just saw the ceiling fan and came back.

647
00:33:29,370 --> 00:33:32,910
Guys, I've a really exciting plan for today. - What?

648
00:33:33,040 --> 00:33:35,000
What are you planning without me?

649
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:36,120
You're also part of it.

650
00:33:36,250 --> 00:33:39,620
We're all going.. deep-sea diving.

651
00:33:39,660 --> 00:33:41,000
Wow.. - Nice.

652
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:43,620
One minute. I can't come.

653
00:33:43,750 --> 00:33:44,540
Why? - Why?

654
00:33:44,620 --> 00:33:46,370
I'm scared of deep water.

655
00:33:46,870 --> 00:33:49,120
I am scared of the sea, Adi. - What?

656
00:33:49,250 --> 00:33:51,620
Adi, you didn't know Riya's scared of deep water.

657
00:33:51,870 --> 00:33:53,910
We don't bathe together that I would know.

658
00:33:57,870 --> 00:33:59,120
I am sorry, Riya.

659
00:33:59,290 --> 00:34:02,620
Come on, we'll be together. - No, no, no.

660
00:34:02,870 --> 00:34:04,660
Are you sure? - Yes, baby.

661
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:09,370
You guys go. And you guys have lots of fun. - Yes.

662
00:34:09,790 --> 00:34:10,870
I'll see you later.

663
00:34:11,160 --> 00:34:12,910
Bye. - Bye.

664
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:16,660
Come soon, I'll get Anushka and see you guys.

665
00:34:17,370 --> 00:34:18,040
Done.

666
00:34:23,910 --> 00:34:25,500
Anushka, where are you?

667
00:34:25,790 --> 00:34:27,620
I've just come into the lobby.

668
00:34:28,540 --> 00:34:29,870
I am in the lobby as well.

669
00:34:53,790 --> 00:34:54,870
Are you okay?

670
00:34:56,250 --> 00:34:57,500
Are you okay?

671
00:34:57,870 --> 00:34:58,620
Yeah.

672
00:34:58,870 --> 00:34:59,750
Then hang up.

673
00:35:02,660 --> 00:35:05,870
Ma'am, your car is ready. - Thank you.

674
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,290
Anushka - What?

675
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:12,120
Are you going somewhere? - Yes.

676
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:14,250
I made plans for deep-sea diving, with you.

677
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:15,750
The entire gang's waiting.

678
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:18,620
I can't come. I'm going to pick up Jay.

679
00:35:18,750 --> 00:35:21,000
Oh..you're looking really hot. - Thank you.

680
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:23,370
Yeah, Anushka..you're looking like a woman. - Hey..

681
00:35:23,870 --> 00:35:26,120
But how are you going to jump in the water in these clothes?

682
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:27,660
She isn't jumping in the water. - Why?

683
00:35:27,750 --> 00:35:28,370
She's not coming with us.

684
00:35:28,500 --> 00:35:29,370
What? - Why?

685
00:35:29,500 --> 00:35:31,500
What do you mean? Jay's coming.

686
00:35:31,540 --> 00:35:33,250
I am going to the airport to pick him up.

687
00:35:33,370 --> 00:35:35,160
Let's send a car to pick up Jay.

688
00:35:35,250 --> 00:35:37,540
Jay's coming here to marry me, not the car.

689
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:40,910
Anushka isn't coming either. Nor is Riya.

690
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:44,620
Idea! Why don't we all go pick up Jay?

691
00:35:44,870 --> 00:35:45,750
What an idea?

692
00:35:45,750 --> 00:35:46,870
Anushka, do you mind?

693
00:35:47,540 --> 00:35:48,620
Of course I mind.

694
00:35:48,660 --> 00:35:51,290
We don't care. - Come on, guys, let's go.

695
00:35:54,160 --> 00:36:01,120
We'll never break this friendship.

696
00:36:01,160 --> 00:36:02,790
We'll give up..

697
00:36:02,870 --> 00:36:03,620
What's that?

698
00:36:03,660 --> 00:36:05,410
Anushka, turn left.. turn left.

699
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:07,250
What's that board? - I don't know.

700
00:36:07,750 --> 00:36:09,410
It has your name written on it.

701
00:36:09,660 --> 00:36:11,910
Are you guys playing some kind of prank on me? - No way.

702
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:13,870
What can be a bigger prank than you getting married.

703
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,040
I think we should find out.

704
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:16,910
Yeah, let's go.

705
00:36:18,870 --> 00:36:20,250
Something's definitely wrong.

706
00:36:20,290 --> 00:36:22,250
First left, now right. What's going on here?

707
00:36:22,290 --> 00:36:24,250
Anushka, turn left.

708
00:36:25,370 --> 00:36:26,750
So many balloons.

709
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,370
Something's definitely wrong.

710
00:36:34,370 --> 00:36:35,790
Jay! Oh my God.

711
00:36:35,870 --> 00:36:36,870
Get down.

712
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:38,750
Batli, get down.

713
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:43,660
Jay. - Anushka.

714
00:36:45,750 --> 00:36:47,750
When did you get so filmy?

715
00:36:50,750 --> 00:36:53,870
My God..this is so special.

716
00:36:53,910 --> 00:36:55,660
It is for my most special lady.

717
00:36:55,750 --> 00:36:57,000
My most beautiful.

718
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:01,370
How sweet. But how did you arrange all this?

719
00:37:02,250 --> 00:37:03,870
With the help of a genie.

720
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:09,370
That I should've guessed.

721
00:37:09,870 --> 00:37:10,910
Thank you.

722
00:37:12,660 --> 00:37:15,290
Oh..this is called love.

723
00:37:20,870 --> 00:37:22,870
This is called love at first sight.

724
00:37:23,660 --> 00:37:25,750
Not first, it's second sight.

725
00:37:25,870 --> 00:37:28,250
She's the girl we saw on Skype. - Yeah.

726
00:37:28,500 --> 00:37:29,500
Why are you guys standing there?

727
00:37:29,620 --> 00:37:30,910
Come meet Jay. - Hi, Jay.

728
00:37:31,370 --> 00:37:33,120
Hi, Jay. How are you?

729
00:37:33,370 --> 00:37:34,500
How was the flight?

730
00:37:34,910 --> 00:37:38,370
Hi, Jay. Finally. - Yeah, finally.

731
00:37:38,910 --> 00:37:39,660
Well, those are my friends.

732
00:37:39,750 --> 00:37:41,040
Derek, Paula and Roxie.

733
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:41,500
Hi.

734
00:37:41,540 --> 00:37:42,500
Hi. - Roxie.

735
00:37:44,250 --> 00:37:46,290
Hi. - I love you.

736
00:37:46,790 --> 00:37:48,750
I knew it..

737
00:37:48,870 --> 00:37:49,750
I love you.

738
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:51,870
How's Gulabo? - She's good. Let's go meet her.

739
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:52,870
Let's go to the hotel.

740
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:53,500
Yeah..

741
00:37:53,540 --> 00:37:54,870
Nice guy, huh.

742
00:37:55,370 --> 00:37:56,370
What do you say, sir?

743
00:37:57,750 --> 00:38:00,540
Your arrangement was fantastic. - Well, thank you, sir.

744
00:38:00,620 --> 00:38:01,620
Excuse me.

745
00:38:14,910 --> 00:38:18,870
Sweety, what song did you select for our dance?

746
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,410
I was thinking about that old number.

747
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:25,120
Everyone's been talking about our love.

748
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:27,160
Sweety, what a selection.

749
00:38:27,620 --> 00:38:28,250
Thank you.

750
00:38:28,410 --> 00:38:30,500
You remember. - Why wouldn't I?

751
00:38:30,620 --> 00:38:34,120
I would always stare at Mumtaz's hairstyle.

752
00:38:34,160 --> 00:38:36,540
And I was looking at her tight sari.

753
00:38:36,620 --> 00:38:39,620
What? - It was too tight, that's why.

754
00:38:51,410 --> 00:38:52,290
See that.

755
00:38:55,540 --> 00:38:57,370
She's teaching her father to dance.

756
00:38:58,870 --> 00:39:01,250
You know..she's going to make you dance to her tunes as well.

757
00:39:03,250 --> 00:39:07,000
Forget about me..tell your partner to rehearse for the dance.

758
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:10,250
Jay doesn't need to rehearse, okay. - I see.

759
00:39:10,620 --> 00:39:12,500
When Jay and I come on the dance floor..

760
00:39:12,540 --> 00:39:15,120
..we're going to be so awesome, everyone will be mesmerized.

761
00:39:17,910 --> 00:39:20,120
I can't do it. I can't do it.

762
00:39:20,290 --> 00:39:22,910
Papa, mom has already learned all the dance steps.

763
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:25,620
If she dances better than you, will you be able to take it?

764
00:39:25,660 --> 00:39:30,000
What? Your mom's going to dance too? - Yes. With you.

765
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:32,790
This must be her idea.

766
00:39:32,870 --> 00:39:34,790
She always wants to make me dance to her tune.

767
00:39:34,870 --> 00:39:36,790
Papa, it's my idea.

768
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:40,910
Dear..I thought you're smart..like me.

769
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:43,290
Papa, please. Enough talking, and start dancing.

770
00:39:43,410 --> 00:39:45,250
Come on, like this.

771
00:39:45,290 --> 00:39:47,370
Since mom's dancing, I will have to.

772
00:39:47,500 --> 00:39:50,370
3.. 4.. 5.. 6..

773
00:39:50,500 --> 00:39:51,290
Very good.

774
00:39:51,370 --> 00:39:52,370
Again.

775
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:55,410
Batli, teach me properly.

776
00:40:12,120 --> 00:40:13,660
Ladies and Gentlemen.

777
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:16,750
First of all, let's begin with applauding for the two lovely couples..

778
00:40:16,910 --> 00:40:18,540
..whose wedding you're here for.

779
00:40:18,790 --> 00:40:20,040
Adi and Riya.

780
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,250
Congratulations, guys.

781
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:24,500
Thanks.

782
00:40:24,620 --> 00:40:25,660
Anushka and Jay.

783
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:29,500
Jay..

784
00:40:29,620 --> 00:40:31,370
Thank you, people.

785
00:40:31,910 --> 00:40:35,250
A poet once said that marriage is like an old wine.

786
00:40:35,290 --> 00:40:36,040
Well said!

787
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:39,500
The older it gets, the more high it gets you.

788
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:40,750
Yeah right.

789
00:40:40,790 --> 00:40:43,120
Well, according to me, Mr. Kapoor..

790
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:44,750
..marriage is like a chewing gum.

791
00:40:46,410 --> 00:40:49,250
In the beginning it tastes sweet.

792
00:40:49,290 --> 00:40:52,660
But later it tastes like rubber.

793
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,540
Maybe you're right, Mr. Sodhi.

794
00:40:54,790 --> 00:40:56,410
Let's see how sweet your chewing gum..

795
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:59,290
I mean your marriage still is.

796
00:40:59,500 --> 00:41:01,040
This is the theme of the party.

797
00:41:01,290 --> 00:41:03,750
How well do you know your partner?

798
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:08,870
So..Mr. Sodhi, do you remember your first meeting with Sweety?

799
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:12,000
I do, Mr. Kapoor, I still do.

800
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:16,750
Sweety was wearing a red color sari.

801
00:41:17,370 --> 00:41:19,250
I should've understood that..

802
00:41:19,500 --> 00:41:21,790
..it's a sign of danger. - Oh, Lord!

803
00:41:21,870 --> 00:41:23,250
Mr. Kumar. - Yeah.

804
00:41:23,410 --> 00:41:26,790
When you met Amrita for the first time, how was she looking?

805
00:41:27,370 --> 00:41:30,370
Mr. Kapoor, what did you just ask?

806
00:41:30,790 --> 00:41:32,870
You should've asked him something business related..

807
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,620
..and he would've replied promptly.

808
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:37,040
But he won't remember our first meeting.

809
00:41:41,410 --> 00:41:44,120
Well..she was looking beautiful.

